        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 1:53PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 153 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near Belle Center,
moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail may cause minor damage to
vegetation.

Locations impacted include...
Huntsville, Silver Creek, Belle Center, New Jerusalem, Rushsylvania,
Richwood, Zanesfield, Byhalia, Ridgeway, Pfeiffer, Hepburn, Mount
Victory, Mentzer, Northwood, Bellefontaine, Somersville, Big Springs,
Essex, and West Mansfield.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM EDT for
central and west central Ohio.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
